com.bluegosling.collections

Class AbstractRandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.collections.AbstractNavigableMap<K,V>
      • com.bluegosling.collections.AbstractRandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys in the map
    V - the type of values in the map
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    RandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V>, Map<K,V>, NavigableMap<K,V>, SortedMap<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractRandomAccessNavigableMap.RandomAccessSubMap, AbstractRandomAccessNavigableMap.SubMapByIndices

    public abstract class AbstractRandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V>
extends AbstractNavigableMap<K,V>
implements RandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V>
    An abstract base class for RandomAccessNavigableMap implementations. Sub-classes must implement most of the methods needed to implement a normal AbstractNavigableMap. The main differences follow:
    • Methods firstEntry() and lastEntry() do not need to be implemented. This abstract map implements them in terms of random access, e.g. getEntry(0)
    • New random access methods, RandomAccessNavigableMap.getEntry(int) and RandomAccessNavigableMap.removeEntry(int), must be implemented.

      • descendingMap

        public RandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V> descendingMap()
        Description copied from class: AbstractNavigableMap

        This default implementation should suffice for any NavigableMap since the map provides all necessary operations to trivially reverse the order. It simply uses inverse operations to return the descending view of this map. For example, the inverse of NavigableMap.firstEntry() is NavigableMap.lastEntry(), the inverse of the key set's iterator() is its descendingIterator(), etc.

        Specified by:
        descendingMap in interface RandomAccessNavigableMap<K,V>
        Specified by:

        Overrides:
